_:N07a9f1a626fd4e2aafdb55f5b8873ffa <http://schema.org/description> "The Office of the Regulator of Community Interest Companies decides whether an organisation is eligible to become, or continue to be, a community interest company (CIC). It is responsible for investigating complaints - taking action if necessary - and it provides guidance and assistance to help people set up CICs. CIC Regulator works with the Department for Business and Trade ." .
